      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software quality plan with version control, regression testing, and documented release procedures must be in place and verified for the CFD solver used in hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver has basic version control but lacks a formal software quality plan with documented regression testing covering hemolysis-relevant flow regimes. Achieved level 2 is insufficient for MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests and method-of-manufactured-solutions verification must demonstrate correct numerical implementation for turbulent blood flow conditions relevant to the VAD operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Only basic benchmark comparisons were performed. Method of manufactured solutions has not been applied to the hemolysis transport equations. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study following GCI methodology must be performed on hemolysis index QoIs across all 5 operating points, with discretization uncertainty reported and bounded.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted at only one operating point. Discretization error at remaining four operating points is unquantified. Achieved level 2 is insufficient."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match or bound VAD operating conditions in terms of flow rate, rotational speed, hematocrit, and blood analog rheology.",
      "rationale": "Experimental conditions cover three of five target operating points. Hematocrit values in bench tests deviate from clinical range by up to 8%. Achieved level 3 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., E_rel, MAPE) between predicted and measured hemolysis index must be computed with uncertainty bounds for all operating points, and model error must fall within acceptance band.",
      "rationale": "Relative error metrics were computed for three operating points with mean absolute percentage error of 34%, exceeding the 15% acceptance threshold. Two operating points lack experimental counterparts entirely. Achieved level 3 is substantially below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis index QoI used in validation must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint (plasma free hemoglobin rise) and must be computed consistently between simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is used as the primary QoI and is clinically traceable. However, the power-law hemolysis model coefficients are derived from non-VAD literature sources, introducing QoI relevance uncertainty. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on a geometry and flow regime sufficiently similar to the Class III VAD COU to support extrapolation of validation conclusions.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares design topology with the target device. However, the target device impeller geometry differs substantially in blade angle and tip clearance, limiting direct applicability. Achieved level 2 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence errors and floating-point round-off contributions to hemolysis index predictions must be characterized and shown to be negligible relative to other uncertainty sources.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error has not been assessed. Residual convergence criteria are reported but no formal analysis of solver-induced error contributions to hemolysis QoI has been performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Potential for analyst use error in model setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing of hemolysis results must be assessed through independent review or round-robin exercise.",
      "rationale": "No independent review or round-robin exercise has been conducted. Use error assessment has not been initiated. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selection of turbulence model, hemolysis damage accumulation model, and constitutive blood rheology model must be justified relative to the VAD flow regime and the model form uncertainty must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty arising from turbulence closure (SST k-omega) and power-law hemolysis model selection has not been formally quantified. No alternative model form comparison has been performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (viscosity parameters, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profiles) must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated through the model via Monte Carlo or equivalent.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but only two of seven identified uncertain input parameters were included in the propagation. The hemolysis model coefficients, which dominate output uncertainty, were treated as fixed. Flagged as incomplete epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The number and selection of experimental test samples must be sufficient to characterize biological variability in hemolysis response and support statistical comparison with model predictions.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data are available from a single test campaign with n=3 replicates per operating point. Sample size is insufficient to characterize inter-donor biological variability. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions and material properties used in the CFD model must be demonstrated to be equivalent to those present in the physical validation experiments within quantified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of inlet boundary conditions between CFD setup and experimental rig has not been formally documented. Pump inlet swirl and velocity profile differences between simulation and experiment are uncharacterized. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    }
